<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[813,1456,1396,2030]" box="[813,913,1396,1422]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[813,1456,1396,2030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">
<bibRefCitation author="GOOD R. D." box="[813,969,1429,1456]" journalOrPublisher="Suppl." pageId="12" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 40" part="2" refId="ref8747" refString="GOOD R. D. 1926. - Mr. John Gossweiler's plants from Angola and Portuguese Congo. Journal of Botany 64, Suppl. 2: 1 - 40." title="Mr. John Gossweiler's plants from Angola and Portuguese Congo. Journal of Botany 64" type="journal article" year="1926">Good (1926)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName box="[1097,1390,1429,1455]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="microphylla">
<emphasis box="[1097,1390,1429,1455]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Pauridiantha microphylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName box="[813,963,1461,1487]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canthiiflora">
<emphasis box="[813,963,1461,1487]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">P. canthiiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on account of its smaller leaves with different venation, but these characters are not reliable. The key in 
<bibRefCitation author="NTORE S." box="[842,984,1525,1551]" journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 227" part="15" refId="ref9107" refString="NTORE S. 2008. - Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae). Opera Botanica Belgica 15: 1 - 227." title="Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2008">Ntore (2008</bibRefCitation>
: 60-61) separates them based on the calyx (“cupuliforme” vs “denté ou lobé”) and 
<typeStatus box="[1268,1316,1557,1583]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">type</typeStatus>
of domatia, which are not reliable either: both taxa actually have similar domatia, i.e. crypt-like and masked by a tuft of hairs. No additional differences have been found, so the two taxa are synonymised here, which extends the range of 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1456,1684,1710]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canthiiflora">
<emphasis box="[1311,1456,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">P. canthiiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[843,922,1716,1742]" name="Angola" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Angola</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingCountry box="[938,1041,1716,1743]" name="Angola" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Cabinda</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[813,1456,1396,2030]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">
The original description of 
<taxonomicName box="[1128,1273,1748,1774]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Pauridiantha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Gentianales" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canthiiflora">
<emphasis box="[1128,1273,1748,1774]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">P. canthiiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not cite the type specimen, but 
<emphasis box="[1020,1133,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">Mann 167</emphasis>
is the only possible candidate, and has always been considered as the type by subsequent authors (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="HALLE N." bookContentInfo="278 p." box="[962,1090,1843,1869]" editor="AUBREVILLE A." journalOrPublisher="Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" refId="ref8779" refString="HALLE N. 1966. - Famille des Rubiacees (1 ere partie), in AUBREVILLE A. (ed.), Flore du Gabon. Vol. 12. Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, Paris, 278 p." title="Famille des Rubiacees (1 ere partie)" type="book" volumeTitle="Flore du Gabon. Vol. 12" year="1966">Hallé 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="NTORE S." box="[1106,1239,1844,1870]" journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 227" part="15" refId="ref9107" refString="NTORE S. 2008. - Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae). Opera Botanica Belgica 15: 1 - 227." title="Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2008">Ntore 2008</bibRefCitation>
). This collection is represented by three sheets in different herbaria. 
<bibRefCitation author="NTORE S." journalOrPublisher="Opera Botanica Belgica" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 227" part="15" refId="ref9107" refString="NTORE S. 2008. - Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae). Opera Botanica Belgica 15: 1 - 227." title="Revision du genre afrotropical Pauridiantha (Rubiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2008">Ntore (2008</bibRefCitation>
: 82) cited the K sheet as 
<typeStatus box="[1157,1259,1907,1933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">holotype</typeStatus>
, which is an error since no herbarium of deposit was cited in the protologue; this sheet is here selected as 
<typeStatus box="[1132,1237,1971,1997]" pageId="12" pageNumber="39">lectotype</typeStatus>
, since it is the only one annotated by 
<bibRefCitation author="HOOKER J. D." box="[1016,1189,2003,2030]" editor="BENTHAM G." journalOrPublisher="Lovell Reeve &amp; Co., Williams &amp; Norgate, London" pageId="12" pageNumber="39" pagination="7 - 151" refId="ref8906" refString="HOOKER J. D. 1873. - Ordo LXXXIV: Rubiaceae, in BENTHAM G. &amp; HOOKER J. D. (eds), Genera Plantarum: ad exemplaria imprimis in Herbariis Kewensibus servata definita. Volume 2, part 1. Lovell Reeve &amp; Co., Williams &amp; Norgate, London: 7 - 151. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 747" title="Ordo LXXXIV: Rubiaceae" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Genera Plantarum: ad exemplaria imprimis in Herbariis Kewensibus servata definita. Volume 2, part 1" year="1873">Hooker (1873)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
